# Frontend replication (web and mobile)

This project has **two frontend codebases**: `apps/web` (Vite + React, desktop + mobile web) and `apps/mobile` (Expo / React Native for iOS/Android). There are no shared packages; each app has its own types, API client, and components.

**Rule:** When adding or changing UI or features in `apps/web`, replicate the same behavior and flows in `apps/mobile` (using React Native primitives and Expo). When changing `apps/mobile`, keep feature parity with `apps/web`. Keep screens, flows, and API usage in sync across both apps.

**What to replicate:**
- Screens and flows (auth, home, place detail, groups, profile, settings, etc.)
- API client calls and types (same endpoints and shapes)
- Navigation structure (same route/screen names and params where applicable)

**What may differ:**
- Implementation: web uses React + DOM + Tailwind; mobile uses React Native + Expo (View, Text, StyleSheet, etc.).
- App-specific config (e.g. Expo config, native env, build config)
- Environment variable names or loading
- Deployment or run scripts

After editing one app, update the other so both stay in sync.
